The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | IOC warns Thanou
                                                                                                                                                                                                     OLYMPIC DIGEST
                      
	IOC warns Thanou  
	Athens: Sprinter Katerina Thanou was named on Monday in the Greek team for the Beijing Olympics setting up a potential confrontation with the IOC. The IOC has warned Thanou that she would face a disciplinary review to examine her eligibility for the Games if she were named in the squad. Thanou and fellow sprinter Costas Kenteris were banned for two years after missing a drugs test on the eve of the Athens Games. On Monday, the Hellenic Olympic Committee (HOC) officially entered Thanou as Greeces 100m representative in Beijing.  
	Biker banned         
	Copenhagen: A mountain biker, Peter Riis Andersen, in Denmarks Olympic team has tested positive for the banned blood-boosting drug EPO before the Games, the Danish National Olympic Committee said.         
	Cycling bribe         
	Japan:A BBC investigation has raised concerns that a cycling event may have bought its way into the Olympic Games. Documents given to the BBC suggest that $3m was paid by organisers of a Japanese cycling event to the UCI         
	Pervez to attend         
	Islamabad: Pakistan president Pervez Musharraf will attend the opening ceremony of the Olympic Games in Beijing and will hold talks with his Chinese counterpart to provide further impetus to bilateral ties.         
	 Leaders from various countries have confirmed their participation at the Games ceremonies.         
